  "detailedRequirements": "<h2>Background</h2>\nThe submission processor sends confirmation emails at the end of the process to inform members if the submission was successfully processed or not, the issue is, during peak traffic times, the submission may stay in a queue for a while and take several minutes to actually be processed, and the members don&#39;t know what is going on in the system. To give transparency to the process, reduce frustration, and reduce support inquiries, we want to send the members an email message immediately when the submission status is changed from INITIATED to PROCESS_PENDING, which is when the upload is complete and the submission is ready to start being processed.\n\n<h2>Scope</h2>\nThis needs to happen in the submission microservice, when the submission record is updated. Messages are sent by simply dropping a message into Kafka. Follow this as an example:<br />\n<br />\nap-submission-processor/blob/dev/service/src/main/java/com/appirio/submissionprocessor/processors/ErrorProcessor.java#L64<br />\n<br />\nMessages have a type, those are mapped to sendgrid templates. We will handle the sendgrid part internally, the goal of this challenge is just to put the message in Kafka. The message type should be &quot;submissionreceived&quot;\n<h2>About Testing</h2>\nPlease follow&nbsp;https://github.com/appirio-tech/tc-common-tutorials/tree/master/submission-system to setup the local environment for testing, the related source code will be attached in forum.<br />\n<br />\nFor verification, you need to check the kafka queue to ensure the message is present.<br />\n&nbsp;",
